      "content": "but i don't want to define anything. there's no 'me' left to define. it feels like the part of me that actually lived died with him. i'm just a shell. i look at the bed, i look at his empty chair, and i just don't see the point in eating or sleeping or even breathing if it's just to sit in this emptiness. it feels like i'm just waiting for something to end.",
